devdoc.author: Michel Massaad
devdoc.details: Implements transaction limits, a global deposit cap, custom errors, and follows security best practices.

params.errorData: The data returned by the failed call.

params.user: The address of the user who deposited.
The address of the user who withdrew.

deposit().details: Reverts if the amount is zero or if the deposit would exceed the global bank cap.Follows the checks-effects-interactions pattern.

withdrawal(uint256).details: Reverts if the amount is zero, exceeds the withdrawal limit, or if the user has insufficient balance.Follows the checks-effects-interactions pattern.

params._amount: The amount to withdraw in wei.
